        ''* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *
        ''* Sub/Fn : cmdSaveSettings_Click
        ''* Description : Save Settings into Worksheet NameRange based on Tag of the Control. Tag is set as PropertyName column present in name Range. which is same as Name of the nameRange where that property is stored.
        ''* Created : 08-04-2014 09:20
        ''* Modified: 08-04-2014 09:20
        ''* 02-20-2015 20:21 Added case for "OptionButton"
        ''* 02-22-2015 19:46 Added Save functionality for Column Access Setting
        ''* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *
        'Private Sub cmdSaveSettings_Click()
        ' On Error GoTo Err_cmdSaveSettings_Click
        '
        ' Dim strTag As String
        ' Dim cntrl As control
        ' For Each cntrl In frameSettings.Controls
        ' strTag = cntrl.Tag
        ' Select Case TypeName(cntrl)
        ' Case "TextBox"
        ' Application.Names(strTag).RefersToRange.Value = Trim(cntrl.Text)
        ' Case "CheckBox"
        ' Application.Names(strTag).RefersToRange.Value = cntrl.Value
        ' Case "ComboBox"
        ' Application.Names(strTag).RefersToRange.Value = Trim(cntrl.Text)
        ' Case "OptionButton"
        '
        ' End Select
        ' Next cntrl
        '
        ' If blnColumnAccessSettingForm = True Then
        ' If MsgBox("You are saving Column Access changes. Are you sure?", vbYesNo + vbQuestion, "Save Column Access?") = vbYes Then
        ' Application.Cursor = xlWait
        ' UpdateChangesInMemory
        ' SaveRelationAccess lngColumnAccessTableId
        ' RefreshColumnAccessForm
        ' Application.Cursor = xlDefault
        ' MsgBox "Column Access settings are saved successfully.", vbOKOnly + vbInformation, "Column Access Saved"
        ' End If
        ' End If
        ' Application.Cursor = xlDefault
        ' Exit Sub
        'Err_cmdSaveSettings_Click:
        ' Application.Cursor = xlDefault
        ' MsgBox Err.Description, vbOKOnly + vbCritical, "Error occured in cmdSaveSettings_Click"
        'End Sub
        '
        '
        '

        ' RefreshColumnAccessForm
        'End Sub

        ''* Sub/Fn : ActivateWindow
        ''* Description : Populate and Show the Option dialog. This is called during Desing time, when all Options are displayed.
        ''* Created : 08-04-2014 09:09
        ''* Modified: 08-04-2014 09:09
        ''* 09-28-2014 23:20 Separate list of 'Default Settings Options' is added. Macro call PopulateDefaultSettingsGroupCombo added

        'Public Sub ActivateWindow()
        ' currentTop = START_TOP
        ' currentLeft = START_CONTROL_LEFT
        ' Set showSettingListRange = Application.Names("OptionProperties").RefersToRange
        ' 'PopulatePropertyGroupCombo
        ' PopulateDefaultSettingsGroupCombo
        '
        ' If cboShowSettingGroup.ListCount > 0 And cboShowSettingGroup.ListIndex = -1 Then
        ' cboShowSettingGroup.ListIndex = 0
        ' If lstPropertyNames.ListCount > 0 Then
        ' lstPropertyNames.ListIndex = 0
        ' End If
        ' End If
        '
        ' DrawControlUsingOptionSettings
        '
        ' If frameDesigning.Enabled = True Then
        ' PopulateDesignPad
        ' End If
        ' Me.Show
        'End Sub
        '
        '

        ''* Description :
        ''* Created : 08-04-2014 09:14
        ''* Modified: 08-04-2014 09:14
        ''* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *
        'Function ControlValueByName(ctrl As control, ProcName As String, CallType As VbCallType, Optional Value As Variant) As Variant
        ' Dim res As Variant
        ' Select Case True
        ' Case CallType = VbGet
        ' res = CallByName(ctrl, ProcName, VbGet)
        ' ControlValueByName = res
        ' Exit Function
        ' Case CallType = VbLet
        ' CallByName ctrl, ProcName, VbLet, Value
        ' Case CallType = VbMethod
        ' res = CallByName(Me, ProcName, VbMethod)
        ' ControlValueByName = res
        ' End Select
        'End Function

        ''* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *
        ''* Sub/Fn : PopulatePropertyGroupCombo
        ''* Description : Populate Property Groups into cboShowSettingGroup list.
        ''* Created : 08-05-2014 10:21
        ''* Modified: 08-05-2014 10:21
        ''* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *
        'Public Sub PopulatePropertyGroupCombo()
        ' On Error GoTo Err_PopulatePropertyGroupCombo
        '
        ' Dim propGrouprange As Range
        ' Set propGrouprange = showSettingListRange.Columns(1)
        ' Set propGrouprange = Application.interSect(propGrouprange, propGrouprange.offset(1))
        '
        ' Dim lngCount As Long
        ' Dim colPropertyGroups As Collection
        ' Set colPropertyGroups = GetUniqueValueCollectionFromColumn(propGrouprange, True)
        ' cboShowSettingGroup.Clear
        ' For lngCount = 1 To colPropertyGroups.count
        ' cboShowSettingGroup.AddItem colPropertyGroups.item(lngCount)
        ' Next lngCount
        ' cboShowSettingGroup.ListIndex = -1
        ' Exit Sub
        'Err_PopulatePropertyGroupCombo:
        ' MsgBox Err.Description, vbOKOnly + vbCritical, "Error occured in PopulatePropertyGroupCombo"
        'End Sub
        '
        '

        ' Set propDefaultSettingGroupRange = Application.interSect(propDefaultSettingGroupRange, propDefaultSettingGroupRange.offset(1))
        '
        ' Dim lngCount As Long
        ' Dim colPropertyGroups As Collection
        ' Set colPropertyGroups = GetUniqueValueCollectionFromColumn(propDefaultSettingGroupRange, True)
        ' cboShowSettingGroup.Clear
        ' For lngCount = 1 To colPropertyGroups.count
